voice_to_text: The boy accidentally dropped his phone into the lake. But when he pulled it out, something astonishing happened. The cracked screen repaired itself, and even the cut on his hand healed as if touched by magic. Jack quickly suspected the lake had mysterious power. To test his theory, he gathered all the broken items from home and carried them to the shore. When he returned, every single object looked brand new. The lake truly possessed miraculous healing energy. That night, a wild thought struck him. What if the lake could bring his mother back to life? While the whole house slept, Jack secretly carried his mother's urn to the lake. He didn't realize his sister Lisa was quietly following behind. At the water's edge, Lisa saw him lifting the urn and ran forward in horror to stop him. During their struggle, her sketchbook slipped from her hands and fell into the water. Jack hurried to fish it out with a branch, but then bubbles began to rise from the surface. Sensing something unnatural, he grabbed Lisa and pulled her away. Moments later, the lake roared and churned violently, as if something beneath was awakening. The next morning, their father came to wake the kids as usual. But Jack and Lisa were already up. And in Lisa's eyes there seemed to flicker the shadows of lingering spirit.
